      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this code may be clearer if you make ExtendedOptions its own type.  You\u0027ve got a couple free functions here that are really logically methods on that type: parseExtendedOptions() is rather like a constructor or factory method, and get_opt() too.",
      "revId": "8157a346f3a379a8a2a788b750dfd168dce9239b",
