      },
      "lineNbr": 201,
      "author": {
        "id": 7954
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-02-20T21:09:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To address this and some of the related comments below, how about I refactor this into a class named ExtendedOptions, that lives inside SkCommonFlagsConfig.cpp.  That class could have a constructor that takes an SkString and parses them into an internal private SkTHashMap\u003cString,String\u003e.  This class could implement accessors (returns a bool to denote presence/absence, out parameters to store values) for each of the parse types, so e.g. parse_option_int would become get_option_int, parse_option_gpu_api would become get_option_gpu_api, etc.  All the out parameters would be typed in the method signatures, which would also obviate the need for using varargs.  Thoughts?",
      "parentUuid": "59dbbeda_e0bc22c7",
      "revId": "8157a346f3a379a8a2a788b750dfd168dce9239b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
